                            left his monastery in the same manner as his fellow monastic <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2032">Qashish</persName> 
                            to travel alone to the eastern, southern, and western regions
                            in the capacity of a wandering monk (aksnāyutā) for many years, 
                            while both let their hair grow long in a worldly fashion, 
                            lest they be honored as monks.
                        </desc>
